  "prompt": "What is the procedure to register a startup company for \"Startup India\" campaign and how much will it benefit a startup?",
  "response": "To register a startup under the \"Startup India\" campaign, here's the comprehensive procedure and benefits:\n\nRegistration Procedure:\n1. Eligibility Criteria\n- Company age: Less than 10 years old\n- Annual turnover less than \u20b9100 crore\n- Incorporated as Private Limited/Partnership/LLP\n- Registered in India\n- Working towards innovation/scalability\n\n2. Online Registration Steps\n- Visit: https://www.startupindia.gov.in\n- Click \"Register Now\"\n- Fill detailed application form\n- Upload required documents\n- Submit for verification\n\nRequired Documents:\n- Incorporation certificate\n- PAN card\n- Company profile\n- Recommendation letter\n- Detailed business plan\n- Proof of concept\n\nBenefits:\n1. Financial Benefits\n- Tax exemption for 3 years\n- Easier access to funding\n- Government grants\n- Reduced compliance burden\n\n2. Networking Benefits\n- Investor connections\n- Mentorship programs\n- Industry networking events\n\n3. Legal Benefits\n- Simplified compliance procedures\n- Fast-track patent registration\n- Easier IPR protection\n\n4. Other Advantages\n- Self-certification compliance\n- Credit guarantee schemes\n- Relaxed procurement norms\n\nRegistration is free and typically takes 2-4 weeks for approval.",
